lead_paragraph: South Africa's JP Duminy and Dean Elgar both scored centuries in a third-wicket partnership of 250 to drive the tourists to a 388-run lead over Australia at the end of the third day of the first test on Thursday.

headline.print_headline: Duminy, Elgar Centuries Put South Africa on Top
